Saturday, July 6 was a memorable day in the lives of the Duke and Duchess of Sussex – Prince Harry and Meghan Markle as baby Archie got christened. Archie Harrison Mountbatten-Windsor was christened in the Private Chapel at Windsor Castle at an intimate service officiated by the Archbishop of Canterbury, Justin Welby. The Royal Family shared photos from the day on Instagram thanking everyone for their love and support since the birth of their baby. See photos below: Queen Elizabeth, Prince Charles and Camille, Duke and Duchess of Cambridge – Prince William and Kate Middleton, Duke and Duchess of Sussex – Prince Harry and Meghan Markle | Photo credit: Instagram/SussexRoyal/Chris Allerton  